    <!-- Chosen Palette: Earthy Calm -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A two-column dashboard layout is used to present the 'Theory' and 'Lab' components side-by-side for easy comparison on larger screens, stacking vertically on mobile. This structure was chosen because the source report has a clear binary division. The primary interaction is visual: donut charts provide an immediate overview of grade distribution, while detailed cards below offer specific information. This allows users to quickly grasp the big picture and then drill down into details as needed, creating a more intuitive and less linear experience than a simple table. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Theory/Lab Grade Distribution: Report Info -> Component Weightings (e.g., Mid-Term 30%). Goal -> Compare/Show Composition. Viz -> Donut Chart. Interaction -> Hover tooltips. Justification -> Excellent for showing parts of a whole in a visually engaging way. Library -> Chart.js (Canvas).
        - Assessment Details: Report Info -> Specifics like quiz topics. Goal -> Inform/Organize. Viz -> Styled Cards. Interaction -> Subtle hover effects. Justification -> Cleaner and more modern layout than a table for presenting detailed text. Method -> HTML/Tailwind.
        - Final Lab Project Breakdown: Report Info -> Report (10%) vs. Presentation (20%). Goal -> Inform/Show Proportion. Viz -> Styled horizontal bar. Interaction -> None needed. Justification -> A simple, lightweight visual element using HTML/CSS is sufficient to show this simple 2-part breakdown without the overhead of a full chart. Method -> HTML/Tailwind.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
